# Implementation Plan - Prompt Configuration UI

The goal is to allow users to configure the AI prompts (Analyst, Strategist, Writer, Editor) directly from the UI, rather than having them hardcoded in the backend.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change moves prompts from [backend/services/chains.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexuslite/backend/services/chains.py) to a JSON file `backend/data/prompts.json`.
> - The initial migration will copy current hardcoded prompts to this JSON file.
> - [chains.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexuslite/backend/services/chains.py) will be refactored to load prompts dynamically.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [NEW] [backend/data/prompts.json](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexuslite/backend/data/prompts.json)
- Store the 4 template strings: `analyst`, `strategist`, `writer`, `editor`.

#### [NEW] [backend/services/prompts.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexuslite/backend/services/prompts.py)
- Service to handle reading/writing the JSON file.
- `get_all_prompts()`
- `update_prompt(key, new_template)`
- Default initialization if file doesn't exist (using current hardcoded values).

#### [NEW] [backend/api/prompts.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexuslite/backend/api/prompts.py)
- FastAPI router.
- `GET /`: Returns all prompts.
- `POST /`: Updates prompts.

#### [MODIFY] [backend/services/chains.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexuslite/backend/services/chains.py)
- Remove hardcoded `ChatPromptTemplate` definitions.
- Export functions `get_analyst_chain()`, `get_strategist_chain()`, etc.
- These functions will:
    1. Fetch the latest prompt string from `services.prompts`.
    2. Create a `ChatPromptTemplate`.
    3. Return the chain (`prompt | llm | parser`).

#### [MODIFY] [backend/api/ingest.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexuslite/backend/api/ingest.py)
- Update usages of `chains.analyst_chain` to `chains.get_analyst_chain()`.

#### [MODIFY] [backend/main.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexuslite/backend/main.py)
- Register the new `prompts` router.

### Frontend

#### [NEW] [frontend/lib/api.js](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexuslite/frontend/lib/api.js)
- Helper functions to fetch and save prompts.

#### [NEW] [frontend/app/prompts/page.js](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexuslite/frontend/app/prompts/page.js)
- New page for editing prompts.
- Fetch prompts on load.
- Render text areas for each prompt.
- "Save Configuration" button.

#### [MODIFY] [frontend/app/page.js](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexuslite/frontend/app/page.js)
- Add a "Configure Prompts" button/link to navigate to `/prompts`.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  **Check Defaults**: Start backend. Ensure `backend/data/prompts.json` is created with default values.
2.  **UI Check**: Navigate to `http://localhost:3000/prompts`. Verify default prompts are loaded.
3.  **Edit & Save**: Change the "Analyst" prompt (e.g., add a specific instruction like "Start response with 'ANALYSIS:'"). Save.
4.  **Verify Persistence**: Restart backend. Reload UI. Verify change persists.
5.  **Functional Test**: Run an ingestion on the main page. Verify the output reflects the prompt change (e.g., check logs or output for "ANALYSIS:").
